{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_83","type":"agent_message","text":"I found the key split in Graal’s substitutions: with build-time-initialized providers, `JceSecurity` caches by provider object identity, so a fresh `new BouncyCastleProvider()` will always miss even if the class name is allowed. With run-time-initialized providers, the cache is keyed by provider name instead, which matches this test pattern. I’m checking whether the repo can enable that future-default for just this library test before I add any helper code."}}
